1
00:00:01,300 --> 00:00:02,960
<i>Previously on Dracula...</i>

2
00:00:03,810 --> 00:00:04,650
Daniel!

3
00:00:06,460 --> 00:00:07,650
...ALECANDER GRAYSON...
...THE WHOLE OF MY WORLD...

4
00:00:07,650 --> 00:00:08,580
Grayson.

5
00:00:08,910 --> 00:00:12,090
I give to you wireless power.

6
00:00:12,760 --> 00:00:15,150
Experiencing some technical difficulties, sir.

7
00:00:15,980 --> 00:00:17,840
- I'd swear. - We've met?

8
00:00:18,190 --> 00:00:20,200
Yes, I was thinking the same thing.

9
00:00:20,890 --> 00:00:23,610
How long must I spend skulking in the shadows?

10
00:00:23,610 --> 00:00:26,920
I wanna walk in the sun like any other man. Sir, the sun.

11
00:00:28,610 --> 00:00:29,530
Damn.

12
00:00:29,810 --> 00:00:32,220
Be my husband, and I will be your wife.

13
00:00:33,000 --> 00:00:35,670
What are you thinking about? You.

14
00:00:35,670 --> 00:00:39,080
I was thinking about Lady Jayne Wetherby and her vampire hunting, of course.

15
00:00:39,080 --> 00:00:44,680
Now that the seers are dead, he will much more easily attract others of his kind.

16
00:00:44,680 --> 00:00:47,340
Soon, London will be crawling with the vermin.

17
00:02:26,690 --> 00:02:29,020
Lady Jayne is a huntsman.

18
00:02:31,090 --> 00:02:34,210
Seems the Ordo Draco is more forward-thinking than I gave it credit for.

19
00:02:35,090 --> 00:02:36,310
Strange times.

20
00:02:37,030 --> 00:02:38,250
Wonderfully strange.

21
00:02:40,570 --> 00:02:43,790
- You'll kill her. - If I kill her,

22
00:02:44,280 --> 00:02:46,520
the Order will just send somebody else to replace her.

23
00:02:47,560 --> 00:02:51,530
You'll end it with her. Now why would I do that?

24
00:02:52,080 --> 00:02:53,640
She's a vampire hunter.

25
00:02:54,140 --> 00:02:58,320
Renfield, not only will I evade her slightest suspicion,

26
00:02:59,870 --> 00:03:02,310
I'll take from her a prize she's given no other man.

27
00:03:04,080 --> 00:03:06,010
Her love. No.

28
00:03:07,330 --> 00:03:08,950
Something far more precious...

29
00:03:10,780 --> 00:03:11,830
Her trust.

30
00:03:15,110 --> 00:03:17,480
Make a reservation tomorrow night,

31
00:03:17,480 --> 00:03:20,550
8:00, for two at the Savoy.

32
00:03:25,020 --> 00:03:27,910
The most exclusive, visible table in the main dining room.

33
00:03:28,250 --> 00:03:29,080
Yes, sir.

34
00:03:46,000 --> 00:03:47,300
Hello, master.

35
00:03:57,840 --> 00:03:59,080
Given the extent of the putrefaction,

36
00:03:59,080 --> 00:04:03,870
I say the female is the youngest, five years sired, maybe less.

37
00:04:03,870 --> 00:04:08,570
This one, on the other hand, is clearly much older, a century undead at least.

38
00:04:08,570 --> 00:04:12,800
I mean, that said, neither of the vampires are old enough to be the ones that killed our seers.

39
00:04:12,900 --> 00:04:14,360
But the one who eluded you?

40
00:04:14,850 --> 00:04:18,200
There, sire, I suspect, which would make him older still.

41
00:04:18,200 --> 00:04:20,020
Old enough to be the one we're searching for?

42
00:04:20,220 --> 00:04:22,530
Oh, he will be a formidable opponent.

43
00:04:23,460 --> 00:04:26,540
Too formidable? If so, Mr. Browning, then God help you,

44
00:04:26,540 --> 00:04:29,280
because if I can't kill the beast, no one can.

45
00:04:32,890 --> 00:04:34,050
Josef Cervenka.

46
00:04:35,390 --> 00:04:36,520
My right hand.

47
00:04:37,870 --> 00:04:38,680
Maybe.

48
00:04:40,050 --> 00:04:41,140
A long time ago.

49
00:04:41,460 --> 00:04:42,520
Nonsense.

50
00:04:43,700 --> 00:04:45,420
You are once more under my battlements.

51
00:04:46,660 --> 00:04:49,740
I summoned you here for a reason, and very soon,

52
00:04:51,110 --> 00:04:54,780
we shall destroy our greatest enemy. The Ordo Draco?

53
00:04:55,080 --> 00:04:55,890
The same.

54
00:04:57,480 --> 00:05:02,280
Rich men who've bet their future on oil, but I've discovered a technology that will destroy them.

55
00:05:02,280 --> 00:05:05,340
But they are stronger than ever. Precisely.

56
00:05:05,340 --> 00:05:09,030
Just this night, I saw two of my brood slaughtered by a huntsman,

57
00:05:10,010 --> 00:05:12,440
a female of all things.

58
00:05:12,880 --> 00:05:14,410
That's why I need your help.

59
00:05:16,280 --> 00:05:17,240
I know her.

60
00:05:19,260 --> 00:05:21,660
Then we will peel the flesh from her bones.

61
00:05:21,720 --> 00:05:22,590
Not yet.

62
00:05:23,380 --> 00:05:25,680
We cannot defeat them by killing them one by one.

63
00:05:26,290 --> 00:05:29,330
We must attack the source of their power. Their wealth.

64
00:05:30,250 --> 00:05:32,020
To pick their pockets like a common thief?

65
00:05:32,020 --> 00:05:35,810
There's no honor in that. I'm sorry, sir. I heard voices.

66
00:05:36,030 --> 00:05:39,690
Renfield, this is my old friend Josef Cervenka.

67
00:05:40,880 --> 00:05:44,450
He will be staying in this house as long as he wishes.

